oai_dc:dc.dc:title: CanaryCulture
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bucci, Toni
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: As the month of June comes to a close,canary breeding here in California is graduallycoming to a close, also. Our ownbreeding of canaries this year, which startedin mid-February, progressed very slowlyand came to its peak in mid-May. Thevery slow start was due to cold, rainyweather which lasted throughout Marchand April. The weather has a great effecton us since our bird room is outdoors.Although completely enclosed, the wallsand ceiling have no insulation whatsoever.I do not recommend this type of abirdroom, but economic and budgetarysituations dictate the present set-up. I donot use any form of artificial heat so thereforemy canaries are exposed to the naturaltemperature fluctuations . Despite ourslow start, we have been doing very wellwith no major disappointments.
